x; margin: 44px 0px 30px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">6 Day Course</span></div><div style=\"color: #44475b; font-weight: 500; font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 24px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Theme: less popular types of equity mutual funds</span></div><div style=\"color: #44475b; width: 100%; height: 0px; border-top: 1px solid grey; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><br></div><!--Thursday Start--><div style=\"font-weight: 500; font-size: 14px; line-height: 24px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px 10px;\">Mon</span><span style=\"margin: 0px 10px;\">Tue</span><span style=\"margin: 0px 10px;\">Wed</span><span style=\"margin: 0px 10px; background: #44475b; color: white; border: 1px solid #44475b; border-radius: 30px; padding: 4px 8px;\">Thu</span><span style=\"margin: 0px 10px; color: #a1a3ad;\">Fri</span><span style=\"margin: 0px 10px; color: #a1a3ad;\">Sun</span></span></div><!--Thursday End--><div style=\"color: #44475b; width: 100%; height: 0px; border-top: 1px solid grey; margin-top: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"color: #44475b; font-weight: 400; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 22px; margin: 20px 0px 16px;\"><p>Value funds.</p><p>These are mutual funds that use the value style of investing.</p><p>In short, they aim to buy stocks that are available at a price that is lower than their fair value.</p><p>Example: the price of a pair of shoes that costs Rs 2,000 is available for Rs 1,300. This can be called a ‘value’ buy.</p><p>These mutual funds try to buy stocks at cheap prices.</p><p>This ‘cheap’ price could be because of several reasons including some temporary market news, temporary reduction in revenues, external factors like global economy, etc.</p><p>Most equity mutual funds use multiple strategies to invest money.</p><p>Mutual funds that invest using only a particular style (like value funds) might give non-consistent returns—very good at some times and very poor at other times.</p></div><div style=\"color: #44475b; width: 5%; height: 0px; border-top: 3px solid black; margin: 24px 0px 16px;\"><br></div><div style=\"color: #7c7e8c; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 20px; font-weight: 400; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Missed last week\'s course? You can download the course PDF - <a href=\"https://groww.weurl.co/lw/g1.jpg?p=eyJsYyI6Imlufjc2YWEzOTIiLCJsIjoiOWU1MTQ4NjBhYWI1MDMwN2YwMThmOTdhYWI0ODJhOWUyZjdmNzNiZSIsImMiOiJkNTcxNjg0Ni05MGM3LTQzNDktYTE5My0zYzY1ZDhkOWRkNWIiLCJlbSI6InBiNTY5OTY5QGdtYWlsLmNvbSIsImUiOiJ%2BMWFma2RrNSIsInYiOiJjcDU2bWQiLCJzIjoifjM5OWZkMWJiOGk4OGlmYl9iNzAzZjM2Zi1jN2U5LTQ1OGMtYTg1My1iNDQwN2EzOGUwNjg6MTcyNzk2ODIzNzAxNiIsImV2ZW50IjoiZW1haWxfY2xpY2siLCJjdGEiOiJ%2BMjVjMTFiNWIiLCJ0b1VSTCI6Imh0dHBzOi8vYml0Lmx5LzNUTnlTR2YifQ%3D%3D\">click to download</a></span></div><div style=\"color: #44475b; font-weight: 500; font-size: 28px; line-height: 24px; margin: 44px 0px 28px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">Featured Question</span></div><table style=\"color: #44475b;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 20%; max-width: 180px;\"></td><td style=\"border: 1px solid #7c7e8c; border-radius: 12px 12px 0px; padding: 20px 16px; font-weight: 500; font-size: 16px; line-height: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Q. “What are Index fund ? How are they different from other mutual fund ?”<br></span></td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"color: #44475b; border: 1px solid #e9e9eb; border-radius: 12px 12px 12px 0px; padding: 20px 16px; margin: 20px 0px; width: 70%; max-width: 420px;\"><div style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #44475b;\">A.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Index funds are a type of mutual fund.</span><p>In case of equity mutual funds, a fund manager chooses which stocks to buy, sell, and continue holding.</p><p>This is called ‘active management’. And such mutual funds are called active mutual funds.</p><p>In index funds, there is no ‘active management’.</p><p>An index fund buys all stocks in a particular index.</p><p>Example: Nifty 50 is made up of 50 of the biggest companies in India.</p><p>A Nifty 50 index fund will invest in all 50 stocks of Nifty 50.</p><p>It will decide the amount of each company\'s stock to buy based on its size.</p><p>The fund manager does not decide which shares to buy.</p><p>This approach is called ‘passive management’.</p><p>Index funds are called ‘passively managed funds’.</p></div></div><div style=\"color: #44475b; width: 5%; height: 0px; border-top: 3px solid black; margin: 24px 0px 16px;\"><br></div><div style=\"color: #7c7e8c; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 8px; font-weight: 400; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">In this section, daily, we\'ll try to answer one burning question related to the field of personal finance education.</span></div><div style=\"color: #7c7e8c; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 8px; font-weight: 400; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Remember, NO investment advice &amp; ONLY personal finance education questions.</span></div><div style=\"color: #7c7e8c; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 8px; font-weight: 400; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Ask your question here: <a href=\"https://groww.weurl.co/lw/g1.jpg?p=eyJsYyI6Imlufjc2YWEzOTIiLCJsIjoiOWU1MTQ4NjBhYWI1MDMwN2YwMThmOTdhYWI0ODJhOWUyZjdmNzNiZSIsImMiOiJkNTcxNjg0Ni05MGM3LTQzNDktYTE5My0zYzY1ZDhkOWRkNWIiLCJlbSI6InBiNTY5OTY5QGdtYWlsLmNvbSIsImUiOiJ%2BMWFma2RrNSIsInYiOiJjcDU2bWQiLCJzIjoifjM5OWZkMWJiOGk4OGlmYl9iNzAzZjM2Zi1jN2U5LTQ1OGMtYTg1My1iNDQwN2EzOGUwNjg6MTcyNzk2ODIzNzAxNiIsImV2ZW50IjoiZW1haWxfY2xpY2siLCJjdGEiOiJ%2BMTkwNGQ4MjMiLCJ0b1VSTCI6Imh0dHBzOi8vdHJ5Z3Jvd3cudHlwZWZvcm0uY29tL3RvL2x3WVRaeXJ1I2VtYWlsbD1wYjU2OTk2OUBnbWFpbC5jb20ifQ%3D%3D\">Ask a question</a></span></div><div style=\"color: #44475b; font-weight: 500; font-size: 28px; line-height: 24px; margin: 44px 0px 30px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">1 Day 